{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Are Branches?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A branch is a lightweight, movable pointer to a commit. Creating a branch is instantaneous \u2014 git just writes a 41-byte reference file. Branches enable parallel development: each feature, bug fix, or experiment lives in isolation until ready to be integrated."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Git branching and merging: feature branch flow vs rebase flow"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branch Commands"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Creating and Switching"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git branch                          # list local branches\ngit branch -a                        # list all (including remotes)\ngit switch -c feature/user-auth      # create + switch (preferred)\ngit checkout -b feature/user-auth    # classic form\ngit switch main                      # switch back to main\ngit branch -d feature/user-auth      # delete (warns if unmerged)\ngit branch -D feature/user-auth      # force delete\ngit push origin --delete feature/x   # delete remote branch\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merging"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merging integrates the history of one branch into another."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast-Forward Merge"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If main has no new commits since the feature branch diverged, git simply moves the pointer forward \u2014 no merge commit is created."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git switch main\ngit merge feature/login          # fast-forward if possible\ngit merge --no-ff feature/login  # force merge commit (recommended for clarity)\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Three-Way Merge"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When both branches have new commits, git finds their common ancestor and creates a merge commit with two parents."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Squash Merge"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Collapses all feature commits into a single commit on main."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git merge --squash feature/login\ngit commit -m \"feat(auth): add login flow\"\n"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strategy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge commit?"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "History"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast-forward"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Linear"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Short-lived branches, no divergence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Three-way --no-ff"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Non-linear, full history"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature branches \u2014 shows where they live"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Squash"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No (one commit)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Linear, compressed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cleaning up noisy wip commits"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebasing"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebasing replays your branch's commits on top of another branch's latest commit, producing linear history. It rewrites commit hashes \u2014 never rebase commits that others have already pulled."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Basic Rebase"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git switch feature/login\ngit rebase main           # replay feature commits on top of latest main\n\ngit fetch origin\ngit rebase origin/main    # rebase onto fetched remote main\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Interactive Rebase"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Interactive rebase lets you edit, squash, reorder, or drop commits before pushing."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git rebase -i HEAD~4     # edit the last 4 commits interactively\n\n# In the editor:\n# pick a3f5b2c  feat: skeleton component\n# squash e7d4a1b  wip: form validation\n# squash f2c8d0a  wip: fix errors\n# pick b1e3c9d  test: unit tests\n\n# Commands: pick | squash | fixup | reword | drop | edit\n"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Command"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Action"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pick"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use commit as-is"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "squash"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge into previous commit; combines messages"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "fixup"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge into previous commit; discard this message"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "reword"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keep commit, edit message"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "drop"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Delete the commit"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "edit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pause to amend the commit"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conflict Resolution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conflicts occur when the same lines were changed on both branches."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conflict Markers"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "typescript"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<<<<<<< HEAD\n  title = 'My Angular App';     // your version (current branch)\n=======\n  title = 'Admin Portal';       // incoming version\n>>>>>>> feature/rebrand\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolution Steps"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Edit the file \u2014 choose a version or combine both; remove all conflict markers."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stage the resolved file: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git add src/app/app.component.ts"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complete: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git commit"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (merge) or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git rebase --continue"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (rebase)."}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git merge --abort    # abandon merge, restore to pre-merge state\ngit rebase --abort   # abandon rebase\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Git Flow Branching Model"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Purpose"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merges into"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "main"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stable, production-ready code"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\u2014"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "develop"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Integration branch, latest delivered changes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "main"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "feature/*"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "New features and components"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "develop"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "release/*"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Release preparation, version bump"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "main and develop"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "hotfix/*"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Critical production fixes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "main and develop"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GitHub Flow (simpler): "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Only two branch types \u2014 main and feature/* \u2014 with all merges going directly into main via pull requests. Preferred for Angular projects that deploy continuously."}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pull Request Workflow"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A Pull Request (PR) is a formal merge request hosted by GitHub/GitLab. It shows the diff, collects review comments, and blocks merge until CI passes."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical Angular PR Flow"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Create branch: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git switch -c feat/JIRA-123-user-profile"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Make commits following Conventional Commits format."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Push: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git push -u origin feat/JIRA-123-user-profile"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Open PR; assign reviewers; link to issue."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI runs: ng lint, ng test, ng build."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Address review comments with additional commits."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Squash-merge into main; delete feature branch."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keeping a PR Up-to-Date"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git fetch origin\ngit rebase origin/main              # replay commits on latest main\ngit push --force-with-lease         # safe force push\n"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Always use --force-with-lease, never --force. "}, {"type": "text", "text": "--force-with-lease checks that no one else pushed to the remote branch since your last fetch. --force overwrites unconditionally and can destroy others' commits."}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Remote Branches and Tracking"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# See all remote-tracking branches\ngit branch -r\n\n# Track a remote branch locally\ngit switch --track origin/feature/user-auth\n\n# View tracking relationships\ngit branch -vv\n\n# Delete a stale remote-tracking reference (remote branch was deleted)\ngit fetch --prune\n\n# Push and set upstream in one step\ngit push -u origin feature/user-auth\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branching Strategy for Angular Monorepos"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large Angular workspaces with multiple apps and libraries benefit from trunk-based development: short-lived feature branches (< 1 week) that merge into main via PRs. Feature flags gate incomplete work in production."}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "nx affected"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to run only tests and builds affected by a change."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tag releases per app: v-admin-2.1.0, v-portal-3.0.0."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Protect main from direct pushes; require PR + CI + review."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use CI path conditions to run only the relevant pipeline per changed app."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "HEAD and Detached HEAD"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "HEAD"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a special pointer that tracks your current position in the repository. Normally HEAD points to a branch name (e.g. main), which in turn points to the latest commit. When HEAD points directly to a commit hash instead of a branch, you are in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "detached HEAD"}, {"type": "text", "text": " state."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# See what HEAD points to\ncat .git/HEAD\n# ref: refs/heads/main   <-- normal\n# a3f5b2c7e1...           <-- detached HEAD\n\n# When does detached HEAD happen?\ngit checkout a3f5b2c         # checking out a specific commit\ngit checkout v1.0.0          # checking out a tag\ngit checkout origin/main     # checking out a remote-tracking branch\n\n# Escape detached HEAD without losing work\ngit switch -c temp-branch    # create a new branch at the current commit\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Upstream Tracking"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every local branch can track a remote counterpart. Once set, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git pull"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git push"}, {"type": "text", "text": " know where to send/receive without arguments."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Set upstream when pushing for the first time\ngit push -u origin feature/login   # -u = --set-upstream\n\n# View tracking configuration\ngit branch -vv\n# * feature/login  a3f5b2c [origin/feature/login: ahead 2] feat(auth): add JWT\n\n# Change tracking to a different remote branch\ngit branch -u origin/develop\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Deleting Stale Remote References"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "After a remote branch is deleted (e.g. merged PR on GitHub), your local remote-tracking references go stale. Clean them up with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git fetch --prune"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git fetch --prune              # remove stale origin/* references\ngit branch -r                  # verify the branch is gone\ngit remote prune origin        # prune without fetching\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bisect: Finding the Breaking Commit"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git bisect"}, {"type": "text", "text": " does a binary search through commit history to find exactly which commit introduced a bug. Invaluable in Angular projects when ng test suddenly starts failing after a long feature branch is merged."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git bisect start\ngit bisect bad HEAD             # current commit is broken\ngit bisect good v1.0.0          # known good state\n\n# git checks out the midpoint commit\n# Run your tests to check if the build passes, then tell git:\ngit bisect good   # or: git bisect bad\n\n# Repeat until git prints the first bad commit\n# Then end the session:\ngit bisect reset\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Advanced: Branch Internals"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Understanding how branches are stored helps demystify git's behaviour."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Every branch is just a file in .git/refs/heads/\ncat .git/refs/heads/main\n# a3f5b2c7e1d4f8b9...  (the SHA-1 of the latest commit)\n\n# A commit object has these fields:\ngit cat-file -p HEAD\n# tree   <SHA of the file tree snapshot>\n# parent <SHA of the previous commit>\n# author  Deiva <dev@example.com> 1735600000 +0000\n# committer ...\n# <blank line>\n# feat(auth): add JWT refresh token support\n"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Because a branch is just a pointer to a commit, and commits store parent pointers, the entire history is a linked list. Merging creates a commit with two parents; rebasing creates new commits with rewritten parent pointers."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conflict Resolution Deep Dive"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "VS Code Three-Way Merge Editor"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "VS Code 1.69+ includes a dedicated three-way merge editor that shows your changes, their changes, and the result side-by-side. Open it by clicking 'Resolve in Merge Editor' above a conflict marker."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Accepting Specific Lines"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Accept all changes from theirs (useful when you want their version)\ngit checkout --theirs src/app/app.component.ts\ngit add src/app/app.component.ts\n\n# Accept all changes from ours (keep your version)\ngit checkout --ours src/app/app.component.ts\ngit add src/app/app.component.ts\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "rerere \u2014 Reuse Recorded Resolution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "rerere"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Reuse Recorded Resolution) remembers how you resolved a conflict and automatically re-applies the resolution next time the same conflict appears \u2014 useful when rebasing a long-lived branch repeatedly."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git config rerere.enabled true   # enable globally\n\n# On next conflict: git rerere automatically applies your saved resolution\n# To clear a bad recorded resolution:\ngit rerere forget src/app/app.component.ts\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Automating Branch Cleanup"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Over time a repository accumulates hundreds of stale feature branches. Automate cleanup in GitHub Actions or add a post-merge hook."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Delete all merged feature branches (local)\ngit branch --merged main | grep -v main | xargs git branch -d\n\n# Delete all remote merged branches (careful \u2014 dry run first)\ngit branch -r --merged origin/main \\\n  | grep -v 'main\\|develop' \\\n  | sed 's/origin\\///' \\\n  | xargs git push origin --delete\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GitHub: Auto-Delete on Merge"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enable 'Automatically delete head branches' in GitHub repo Settings > General > Pull Requests. Every merged PR's branch is deleted automatically."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebase vs Merge: When to Use Each"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scenario"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommended approach"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature branch ready for PR"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Interactive rebase to clean up commits, then PR"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sync feature with latest main (local)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebase \u2014 keeps history linear"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merging a long-lived release branch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge --no-ff \u2014 preserves the release context"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hotfix applied to multiple branches"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cherry-pick the fix commit onto each"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reverting a pushed commit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git revert \u2014 safe, non-destructive"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Undoing local unpushed commits"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git reset --soft HEAD~N"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge Strategies in Detail"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git supports several merge strategies. The default is recursive (now ort in Git 2.34+), but others are available for specific scenarios."}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strategy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "recursive (default)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git merge"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard feature branch merges"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ours"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git merge -s ours other"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Discard all their changes \u2014 record merge but keep your tree"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "octopus"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git merge branch1 branch2 branch3"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge multiple feature branches simultaneously (no conflicts allowed)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "subtree"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git merge -s subtree path"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge a repository as a subdirectory"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Worktrees: Multiple Working Copies"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git worktree"}, {"type": "text", "text": " creates additional working directories linked to the same repository. This lets you check out multiple branches simultaneously \u2014 useful for reviewing a PR while continuing work on another branch."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# List current worktrees\ngit worktree list\n\n# Create a new worktree for branch review/pr-123\ngit worktree add ../review-pr-123 review/pr-123\n\n# Now you can cd into ../review-pr-123 to work on that branch\n# independently \u2014 no stashing needed\n\n# Remove a worktree when done\ngit worktree remove ../review-pr-123\ngit worktree prune    # clean up stale worktree references\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Patch-Based Workflows"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sometimes you need to share changes without direct access to a repository \u2014 for example, when contributing to a project that requires email review (Linux kernel style)."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Export commits as patch files\ngit format-patch HEAD~3  # creates 0001-*.patch, 0002-*.patch, 0003-*.patch\n\n# Apply a patch file\ngit apply 0001-feat-auth.patch\n\n# Apply a series of patch files (preserves commit metadata)\ngit am 0001-*.patch\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Angular Branching Workflows"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Starting a New Feature"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# 1. Make sure main is up to date\ngit switch main\ngit pull origin main\n\n# 2. Create a feature branch from main\ngit switch -c feat/JIRA-456-dark-mode\n\n# 3. Work, commit often\ngit add src/app/theme/\ngit commit -m \"feat(theme): add dark mode CSS variables\"\ngit add src/app/theme/theme.service.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat(theme): add ThemeService with toggle\"\n\n# 4. Push to remote and open PR\ngit push -u origin feat/JIRA-456-dark-mode\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hotfix Workflow"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Create hotfix directly from main (not develop)\ngit switch main\ngit pull origin main\ngit switch -c hotfix/JIRA-789-null-pointer\n\ngit commit -am \"fix(user): guard against null user in ProfileComponent\"\n\n# Merge into main with a version bump\ngit switch main\ngit merge --no-ff hotfix/JIRA-789-null-pointer\ngit tag -a v1.0.1 -m \"Hotfix: null pointer in ProfileComponent\"\ngit push origin main --tags\n\n# Also merge back into develop (or feature branch if applicable)\ngit switch develop\ngit merge --no-ff hotfix/JIRA-789-null-pointer\n\n# Clean up\ngit branch -d hotfix/JIRA-789-null-pointer\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Syncing a Long-Running Feature Branch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Periodically sync your feature branch with main to avoid big conflict bursts\ngit fetch origin\ngit switch feat/JIRA-456-dark-mode\ngit rebase origin/main     # replay feature commits on latest main\ngit push --force-with-lease  # update remote branch\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI Integration with Branches"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Configure your CI pipeline to validate every branch before merging. A typical Angular branch protection setup on GitHub:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# .github/workflows/branch-checks.yml\nname: Branch Checks\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, develop]\n\njobs:\n  validate:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n        with:\n          node-version: '20'\n          cache: 'npm'\n      - run: npm ci\n      - run: npm run lint\n      - run: npm test -- --no-watch --browsers=ChromeHeadless\n      - run: npm run build -- --configuration production\n"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "With this workflow, a PR can only be merged when all three checks (lint, test, build) pass on the branch. Configure these as Required Status Checks in GitHub branch protection settings."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Troubleshooting Common Branching Issues"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Issue"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Symptom"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fix"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Committed to wrong branch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Changes on main instead of feature branch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git reset HEAD~1; git switch -c correct-branch; git stash pop"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Accidentally deleted branch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branch pointer gone but commits exist"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git reflog; git switch -c recovered-branch <SHA>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Diverged from remote"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git pull fails with non-fast-forward"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git pull --rebase or git fetch + git rebase"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebase lost commits"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Interactive rebase dropped a commit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git reflog to find SHA; git cherry-pick to recover"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge into wrong branch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature merged into develop instead of main"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git revert <merge-commit>; re-merge to correct branch"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "reflog: Your Safety Net"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The reflog records every position HEAD has pointed to in the last 90 days. It is your recovery tool when you think you have lost commits:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git reflog                  # show all HEAD movements\n# HEAD@{0}: commit: feat(auth): JWT refresh\n# HEAD@{1}: rebase finished: ...\n# HEAD@{2}: checkout: moving to feature/login\n\n# Recover a commit\ngit switch -c recovery HEAD@{3}\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Summary"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branches are cheap, isolated contexts for parallel Angular development."}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git switch -c feature/x"}, {"type": "text", "text": " creates and checks out; "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git switch main"}, {"type": "text", "text": " returns."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Three merge strategies: fast-forward (linear), three-way (full history), squash (clean single commit)."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebase replays commits on a new base \u2014 only on branches not yet pushed to shared remotes."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Interactive rebase ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git rebase -i HEAD~N"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") polishes commits before opening a PR."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "After rebasing a pushed branch, use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git push --force-with-lease"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolve conflicts by editing markers, staging, and completing the merge or rebase."}]}]}]}]}}